reut2-010.sgm, MALAYSIA EXPECTS RUBBER SHORTAGE IN APRIL/MAY, Malaysia said it expects a naturalrubber shortage in April and May because of the effects ofcurrent wintering on rubber trees.    The expected shortage and stronger demand for rubber goods,especially condoms and surgical gloves by consumers, is likelyto push up prices, the Malaysian Rubber Exchange and LicensingBoard said in its latest monthly bulletin.    During the annual wintering period from February to Aprilrubber trees shed their leaves and latex output is very low. REUTER&#3;
