reut2-010.sgm, NORTH KOREA AGREES TO TOP LEVEL TALKS WITH SOUTH, North Korea said it agreed to a SouthKorean proposal for talks between the prime ministers of thetwo countries, and proposed a preparatory meeting on April 23.    The state-run North Korean Central News Agency, monitoredhere, said Pyongyang signalled its agreement in a letter sentby North Korean prime minister Li Gun-Mo to his southerncounterpart Lho Shin-Yong.    Lho proposed that the two prime ministers meet for talks ina letter on March 17. REUTER&#3;
