reut2-010.sgm, JAPAN ACTIVELY BOUGHT U.S. CORN LAST WEEK - TRADE, Japanese feed and starch makers activelybought U.S. Corn last week, C and F basis, for July/Septembershipment in view of bullish freight rates following activeinquiries by the Soviet Union, trade sources said.    Some said the makers were seen buying some 30 pct of theirrequirements, estimated at about three mln tonnes for thethree-month shipment period.    Belief is growing that freight rates will not declinesharply from current high levels even in the usually sluggishsummer season because the Soviet Union's chartering is seencontinuing five to seven months from April

